Daniel Friedman, Fall 2012
I affirm that I have adhered to the Honor Code in this assignment.
Made for CS357 (Computer Graphics).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

An implementation of the full view transformation (translating world coordinates
to screen (pixel) coordinates) in C, using OpenGL libraries. Draws a simple 3D
cube outline, only drawing upon 2D OpenGL functions. Simple GUI controls gives
the viewer control over the look-at point, viewer position, and view angle
theta.
